<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910812-0067</DOCNO><DOCID>910812-0067.</DOCID><HL>   Texas to Vote on Nov. 5   On Allowing State Lottery</HL><DATE>08/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>CASINOS AND GAMBLING (CNO)ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   AUSTIN, Texas -- Texans will vote Nov. 5 on aconstitutional amendment that would allow the state to starta lottery that could begin operations as soon as next summer.   The vote became a possibility after the state Senate voted22-3 to give final approval to the constitutional amendment.The state's House approved the amendment last week.</LP><TEXT>   Gov. Ann Richards has campaigned hard for the lottery as away to reduce the state's budget deficit. The stateLegislature, however, still is meeting in a special sessionto come up with a tax plan to balance the state's budget.</TEXT></DOC>